Sentence: Is the train late today?
Is : auxiliary verb "be", present tense, third person singular, inverted with subject
the : definite article, singular
train : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "is"
late : adjective, predicative complement
today : adverb of time, modifies the state of being late

Sentence: Do you like spicy food?
Do : auxiliary verb "do", present tense, second person, inverted with subject
you : personal pronoun, second person singular or plural, subject of the verb "like"
like : main verb, base form, transitive
spicy : adjective, modifies "food"
food : common noun, uncountable, direct object of the verb "like"

Sentence: Did she finish the report?
Did : auxiliary verb "do", past tense, inverted with subject
she : personal pronoun, third person singular feminine, subject of the verb "finish"
finish : main verb, base form, transitive
the : definite article, singular
report : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "finish"

Sentence: Are they waiting outside?
Are : auxiliary verb "be", present tense, plural, inverted with subject
they : personal pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "waiting"
waiting : present participle of "wait", forms progressive aspect
outside : adverb of place, modifies "waiting"

Sentence: Has he visited Paris before?
Has : auxiliary verb "have", present tense, third person singular, inverted with subject
he : personal pronoun, third person singular masculine, subject of the verb "visited"
visited : past participle of "visit", forms present perfect tense
Paris : proper noun, city name, direct object of the verb "visited"
before : adverb of time, indicates indefinite past

Sentence: Can we leave early?
Can : modal auxiliary verb, indicates ability or permission, inverted with subject
we : personal pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb "leave"
leave : main verb, base form, intransitive
early : adverb of time, modifies "leave"

Sentence: Would you help me with this?
Would : modal auxiliary verb, indicates polite request, inverted with subject
you : personal pronoun, second person, subject of the verb "help"
help : main verb, base form, transitive
me : personal pronoun, first person singular, indirect object of the verb "help"
with : preposition, introduces the instrument or accompaniment
this : demonstrative pronoun, object of the preposition "with"

Sentence: Will it rain tomorrow?
Will : modal auxiliary verb, indicates future tense, inverted with subject
it : personal pronoun, third person singular neuter, dummy subject for weather
rain : main verb, base form, intransitive
tomorrow : adverb of time, indicates future

Sentence: Does John work here?
Does : auxiliary verb "do", present tense, third person singular, inverted with subject
John : proper noun, masculine, subject of the verb "work"
work : main verb, base form, intransitive
here : adverb of place, modifies "work"

Sentence: Were the students listening carefully?
Were : auxiliary verb "be", past tense, plural, inverted with subject
the : definite article, plural
students : common noun, plural, subject of the verb "listening"
listening : present participle of "listen", forms past progressive aspect
carefully : adverb of manner, modifies "listening"

Sentence: Have they seen the new movie?
Have : auxiliary verb "have", present tense, plural, inverted with subject
they : personal pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "seen"
seen : past participle of "see", forms present perfect tense
the : definite article, singular
new : adjective, modifies "movie"
movie : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "seen"

Sentence: Could she swim across the lake?
Could : modal auxiliary verb, indicates past ability or possibility, inverted with subject
she : personal pronoun, third person singular feminine, subject of the verb "swim"
swim : main verb, base form, intransitive
across : preposition, indicates movement from one side to another
the : definite article, singular
lake : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "across"

Sentence: Is the door locked?
Is : auxiliary verb "be", present tense, third person singular, inverted with subject
the : definite article, singular
door : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "is"
locked : past participle of "lock", functions as adjective describing state

Sentence: Did the package arrive on time?
Did : auxiliary verb "do", past tense, inverted with subject
the : definite article, singular
package : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "arrive"
arrive : main verb, base form, intransitive
on : preposition, part of the phrase "on time"
time : common noun, part of the adverbial phrase indicating punctuality

Sentence: Are we ready to start?
Are : auxiliary verb "be", present tense, plural, inverted with subject
we : personal pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb "are"
ready : adjective, predicative complement
to : particle, introduces the infinitive verb
start : main verb, base form, infinitive
